WEBVTT

00:02.089 --> 00:04.046
- At least the popcorn
was good.

00:04.091 --> 00:05.483
- Coach Kelly should've called
a time-out

00:05.527 --> 00:07.137
after Coolidge missed
that free throw.

00:07.181 --> 00:09.096
- Coach Kelly.
Remember his last year,

00:09.139 --> 00:10.662
when he lost his pen
during gym class?

00:10.706 --> 00:12.969
- He made us walk up and down
the football field

00:13.013 --> 00:14.405
for half an hour,
trying to find it.

00:14.449 --> 00:16.625
- And the whole time,
it was behind his ear.

00:16.668 --> 00:18.670
- [laughs]
You guys wanna come over?

00:18.714 --> 00:19.889
- I have gummies.

00:19.932 --> 00:21.760
- I told my mom
I'd help her make dinner.

00:21.804 --> 00:22.979
- I'll drop you off.

00:23.023 --> 00:25.373
I got a bio test first period,
so.

00:25.416 --> 00:28.158
- Cool, cool. See you tomorrow.

00:33.076 --> 00:36.036
[eerie music]

00:36.079 --> 00:43.217
♪

00:47.482 --> 00:49.745
- Kai's been doing
a lot of weed.

00:49.788 --> 00:51.834
- His dad gets it for him.

00:51.877 --> 00:53.618
- Seriously?
- Yep.

00:53.662 --> 00:55.359
Ever since
the dispensary opened.

00:55.403 --> 00:57.883
His dad thinks it's safer
if he gets it at home

00:57.927 --> 00:59.624
than from some sketch dealer.

00:59.668 --> 01:00.756
- [scoffs]

01:04.760 --> 01:06.370
- Hey.

01:06.414 --> 01:08.981
We should stop
and help him, right?

01:09.025 --> 01:11.201
- Uh, yeah, I guess.

01:11.245 --> 01:14.161
Hi, Ma?
I might be a little late.

01:14.204 --> 01:16.685
We're helping a man
with car troubles.

01:16.728 --> 01:18.382
No, don't worry.

01:18.426 --> 01:20.167
He's, like,
a minister or something.

01:20.210 --> 01:22.517
- Ah, thank you for stopping.

01:22.560 --> 01:24.388
- Yeah, no worries.
What's going on?

01:24.432 --> 01:27.217
- Uh, I just seem
to be stuck in the ditch here.

01:27.261 --> 01:29.872
Can't seem to get back
on the road here.

01:29.914 --> 01:31.134
- Um, okay.

01:31.178 --> 01:32.831
Well, we can try to give you
a push.

01:32.875 --> 01:34.485
- Oh, that would be great.

01:34.529 --> 01:37.097
- Oh, hey, hey, hey,
hey, hey!

01:40.143 --> 01:42.102
- Oh.

01:42.145 --> 01:44.887
- Hey, would you mind
giving us a hand?

01:44.930 --> 01:46.366
- Sure.
I'd be happy to.

01:46.410 --> 01:47.933
- Thanks.
- Oh, God bless.

01:47.977 --> 01:49.326
- Thanks so much.

01:49.370 --> 01:51.110
- Yeah, thank you.

01:51.154 --> 01:52.590
On three?
- Yeah.

01:52.634 --> 01:53.896
- [laughing]

01:53.939 --> 01:55.115
- Give us your phones.

01:55.158 --> 01:56.681
- Oh, my God. Okay, okay.
- Now.

01:56.725 --> 01:58.247
Give me your phone!
- Man, get off!

01:58.292 --> 01:59.554
- Move!
- Okay, okay!

01:59.597 --> 02:01.295
- Go on, get in the van.
- In!

02:01.338 --> 02:02.296
- What do you want?
- In!

02:02.339 --> 02:03.688
- Okay, okay.

02:03.732 --> 02:06.256
Okay, okay.

02:06.300 --> 02:07.605
What do you want? Please!

02:07.649 --> 02:09.085
- What do you want?
What do you want--

02:09.128 --> 02:10.826
- Quiet, little lambs,

02:10.869 --> 02:12.436
or we'll slaughter you both.

02:12.480 --> 02:13.611
- [shakily] Oh, my God.

02:13.655 --> 02:15.483
[gasping]

02:15.526 --> 02:17.702
- No, please!
Please!

02:17.746 --> 02:20.704
[dramatic music]

02:20.749 --> 02:24.318
♪

02:27.495 --> 02:30.324
- I've been diagnosed
with stage III liver cancer.

02:30.367 --> 02:32.587
Lost 20 pounds so far.

02:35.546 --> 02:38.158
Feel so weak,
I can hardly get out of bed.

02:41.161 --> 02:44.164
And my stomach?

02:44.207 --> 02:48.079
Well, it just hurts
all the time.

02:48.124 --> 02:50.692
I'm suffering with this,

02:50.735 --> 02:53.477
suffering bad.

02:53.521 --> 02:57.002
So please, I pray
that you'll let me go home

02:57.046 --> 03:00.005
so I can spend my last time
on this Earth

03:00.049 --> 03:01.442
as a free man.

03:01.485 --> 03:03.835
- Mr. Davis,
if we grant this request,

03:03.879 --> 03:07.665
can we trust you won't resort
to criminal activity again?

03:07.709 --> 03:10.451
- I'm too damn sick
to break any laws.

03:10.494 --> 03:12.148
And just so you know,

03:12.192 --> 03:13.715
I didn't kill that young man,

03:13.758 --> 03:17.675
same as I told everybody
25 years ago.

03:17.719 --> 03:20.939
- I understand we have
a member of the victim's family

03:20.983 --> 03:22.767
who wishes to speak.

03:25.727 --> 03:28.904
Sir, please state your name
for the record

03:28.947 --> 03:31.123
and your relationship
to the victim.

03:31.167 --> 03:33.300
- I'm Remy Scott,
the older brother

03:33.343 --> 03:35.954
of Mr. Davis' victim,

03:35.998 --> 03:38.174
Michael Scott.

03:38.218 --> 03:40.698
- Thank you.

03:40.742 --> 03:42.309
You may proceed.

03:42.352 --> 03:45.180
[quiet dramatic music]

03:45.225 --> 03:46.530
♪

03:46.574 --> 03:50.012
- My brother was...just 18

03:50.055 --> 03:53.972
when he was murdered
in Fort Lauderdale.

03:54.016 --> 03:57.280
Mikey was--

03:57.324 --> 04:00.065
he was the golden child
of our family:

04:00.109 --> 04:03.243
intelligent, funny, kind,

04:03.286 --> 04:06.811
not to mention
a world-class pitcher.

04:06.855 --> 04:08.596
His murder devastated me

04:08.639 --> 04:10.685
and my sister, Claire.

04:10.728 --> 04:12.382
Our parents were never the same

04:12.426 --> 04:14.906
after he came home
from spring break

04:14.950 --> 04:16.255
in a casket.

04:18.127 --> 04:23.350
Mikey was the reason
I became an FBI agent.

04:23.393 --> 04:25.265
I'm now the head
of the Fugitive Task Force,

04:25.308 --> 04:27.702
so I have some insight

04:27.745 --> 04:29.747
into this man
who asks for compassion

04:29.791 --> 04:33.621
but still won't admit
what he did 25 years ago,

04:33.664 --> 04:35.405
when he stabbed
my little brother.

04:35.449 --> 04:37.320
So why should he get mercy now,

04:37.364 --> 04:40.105
when he showed none
for my brother,

04:40.149 --> 04:43.500
when he doesn't have
an ounce of compassion,

04:43.544 --> 04:46.851
when he doesn't have
an ounce of remorse

04:46.895 --> 04:48.026
for what he did

04:48.070 --> 04:51.421
and still has the audacity
to deny it?

04:51.465 --> 04:53.423
Keep this killer in a cage,

04:53.467 --> 04:55.295
where he belongs.

04:56.992 --> 05:00.343
Let justice be served.

05:00.387 --> 05:02.650
♪

05:02.693 --> 05:05.653
[indistinct radio chatter]

05:07.394 --> 05:09.309
- You all right?
You look exhausted.

05:09.352 --> 05:11.485
- Took a redeye last night.

05:11.528 --> 05:13.225
I was down in Florida,
testifying at a hearing

05:13.269 --> 05:14.314
for my brother's case.

05:14.357 --> 05:15.358
- What kind of hearing?

05:15.402 --> 05:16.620
- The guy who killed him
has cancer,

05:16.664 --> 05:18.187
wants to get out of prison
early.

05:18.230 --> 05:19.536
- I'm so sorry.

05:19.580 --> 05:21.016
It's been what, 25 years?

05:21.059 --> 05:22.191
- Yeah.

05:22.234 --> 05:23.366
- So what did they decide?

05:23.410 --> 05:25.063
- We should hear
in the next 48 hours.

05:25.107 --> 05:26.456
What do we got?

05:26.500 --> 05:28.371
- Chloe LeBlanc,
Luke Spottiswood,

05:28.415 --> 05:29.894
sophomores
at the local high school,

05:29.938 --> 05:31.548
last seen leaving
the school parking lot

05:31.592 --> 05:33.594
in Luke's car
after a basketball game

05:33.637 --> 05:34.725
yesterday afternoon.

05:34.769 --> 05:36.466
- You sure this was
an abduction?

05:36.510 --> 05:38.250
Teenagers can be
pretty unpredictable sometimes.

05:38.294 --> 05:39.382
- No, not these two.

05:39.426 --> 05:41.166
I go birding
with Luke's dad, Steven.

05:41.210 --> 05:42.951
These are good kids.

05:42.994 --> 05:44.909
- I found their cell phones
on the ground.

05:44.953 --> 05:46.824
They look like they were
run over by a vehicle.

05:46.868 --> 05:48.522
- And these
were in the car too.

05:48.565 --> 05:49.957
There's nothing
but schoolbooks and papers.

05:50.001 --> 05:51.873
- Dust those phones for prints.
Backpacks too.

05:51.916 --> 05:53.614
- You got it.
- We'll also need photos

05:53.657 --> 05:55.442
of these tire tracks
and any other evidence

05:55.485 --> 05:57.574
that might show up.
- Okay, you got it.

05:57.618 --> 05:59.750
[suspenseful music]

05:59.794 --> 06:02.144
- All right, let's split up
and get these kids home safe.

06:02.187 --> 06:03.667
Hana, Ray, head over
to the high school

06:03.711 --> 06:05.539
for eyewitness
and video leads.

06:05.582 --> 06:07.192
Barnes and I
will cover the parents.

06:07.236 --> 06:13.808
♪

06:15.244 --> 06:17.072
- What are you talking about?

06:17.115 --> 06:20.292
How can our son
just disappear like that?

06:20.336 --> 06:21.772
- Somebody must have seen
something.

06:21.816 --> 06:23.165
- And if they did,
we'll find them.

06:23.207 --> 06:25.036
- Were either of your kids
involved in anything

06:25.080 --> 06:27.169
that might have
precipitated this?

06:27.212 --> 06:28.257
- Like what?

06:28.300 --> 06:29.519
- You're blaming Chloe
for this?

06:29.563 --> 06:30.825
- No.
- No, but we need to know

06:30.868 --> 06:32.000
everything you can tell us.

06:32.043 --> 06:34.394
The important thing
is to remain calm.

06:34.437 --> 06:35.699
- Pfft, sure.
How do we do that?

06:35.743 --> 06:37.092
- What do they want
from us, money?

06:37.135 --> 06:38.789
- Well, no one contacted you,
right?

06:38.832 --> 06:40.400
- We'll post agents
on each of your houses,

06:40.443 --> 06:41.879
just in case.

06:41.923 --> 06:43.098
When's the last time
you spoke with your daughter?

06:43.141 --> 06:45.013
- Chloe called me
after the game was over

06:45.056 --> 06:47.232
and said they had stopped
to help a minister

06:47.276 --> 06:48.408
with car trouble.

06:48.451 --> 06:49.409
- A minister?
Okay, that's good.

06:49.452 --> 06:50.540
Did she say anything else?

06:50.584 --> 06:52.020
- Just that she was with Luke

06:52.063 --> 06:53.282
and she'd be late.

06:53.325 --> 06:54.326
- When do you think
we'll hear something?

06:54.370 --> 06:55.545
- If there are
any developments,

06:55.589 --> 06:56.720
we'll let you know, I promise.

06:56.764 --> 06:58.156
- I can't just sit here
and wait.

06:58.200 --> 06:59.593
I'm gonna drive around
and look for them myself.

06:59.636 --> 07:02.204
- We prefer
that you didn't do that.

07:02.247 --> 07:03.640
I understand
what you're going through.

07:03.684 --> 07:05.425
I've been on the other side
of this myself.

07:07.949 --> 07:10.386
A situation in my own family.

07:10.430 --> 07:13.215
- Oh.
How did that turn out?

07:15.130 --> 07:18.263
- With a happy ending.

07:18.307 --> 07:20.701
- [sighs]

07:23.660 --> 07:26.663
[tense music]

07:26.707 --> 07:33.844
♪

07:34.497 --> 07:37.718
- [panting]

07:39.763 --> 07:41.678
[whispering] Do yours.

08:01.263 --> 08:03.483
- We interviewed
dozens of parents and students

08:03.526 --> 08:04.527
that were leaving
the basketball game

08:04.571 --> 08:05.963
at the same time
as Chloe and Luke.

08:06.007 --> 08:07.530
None of them noticed
anything out of the ordinary.

08:07.574 --> 08:08.662
- But one of Luke's friends
remembered

08:08.705 --> 08:09.924
that after the last home game,

08:09.967 --> 08:11.403
he saw a panel van following
Luke's car

08:11.447 --> 08:12.840
out of the school parking lot.

08:12.883 --> 08:14.145
- There were no vans
in the parking lot yesterday

08:14.189 --> 08:15.756
on the security video.
I'm gonna start grinding

08:15.799 --> 08:17.105
through the other
90 vehicles now.

08:17.148 --> 08:18.498
- Do we have
any security footage

08:18.541 --> 08:19.803
from the last game, the one
where Luke's friend

08:19.847 --> 08:21.152
said he was followed?

08:21.196 --> 08:22.545
- Uh, we should.

08:24.460 --> 08:25.722
Okay, yeah.

08:25.766 --> 08:29.204
This is from a week
before the Coolidge game.

08:30.597 --> 08:32.903
There's a maroon van.

08:32.947 --> 08:34.557
- There's an emblem
on the door.

08:34.601 --> 08:36.211
Looks like a religious symbol.

08:36.254 --> 08:38.299
- The minister
they stopped to help.

08:38.342 --> 08:39.256
- Mm.

08:40.607 --> 08:41.825
The van is registered

08:41.869 --> 08:43.914
to the Sacred Church
of the Revelations,

08:43.957 --> 08:45.786
Dorchester, New Hampshire.

08:45.829 --> 08:48.049
A Jacob Varitek, pastor.

08:48.092 --> 08:51.618
- Dorchester's
40 miles across the state line.

08:51.661 --> 08:53.010
- Get a BOLO out
on that vehicle.

08:53.054 --> 08:54.708
See what we can find
on the pastor.

08:54.751 --> 08:56.492
Gaines and I will cover
Varitek's residence.

08:56.536 --> 08:58.712
Barnes and Ray, I think
you'd be best at the church.

08:58.755 --> 09:02.672
♪

09:02.716 --> 09:04.413
- Pastor Jacob's
not here today.

09:04.456 --> 09:05.588
- Where is he?

09:05.632 --> 09:07.547
- He'll be back
from a funeral tomorrow.

09:07.590 --> 09:08.678
- Who died?

09:08.722 --> 09:10.550
- Little girl in Franconia,

09:10.593 --> 09:12.987
mauled by two pit bulls.

09:13.030 --> 09:15.816
Heard those dogs made
a right good meal of the child.

09:17.078 --> 09:18.949
- You mind if we take
a look inside the church?

09:20.385 --> 09:23.084
- Make it quick.
I'm about to clean up in there.

09:29.612 --> 09:30.961
- Thank you.

09:43.191 --> 09:44.584
Doesn't exactly fill you

09:44.627 --> 09:46.107
with the Holy Spirit in here,
does it?

09:46.150 --> 09:47.674
- You ever been in a church
with an image

09:47.717 --> 09:48.892
of the devil on its walls?

09:48.936 --> 09:50.546
- I guess it makes sense.

09:50.590 --> 09:51.547
Good in the front
of the church,

09:51.591 --> 09:52.679
evil in the back?

09:52.722 --> 09:54.202
- It's giving me the same vibe

09:54.245 --> 09:55.595
like in one
of those voodoo places

09:55.638 --> 09:58.380
in the French Quarter.

09:58.423 --> 09:59.599
It's creepy.

10:02.645 --> 10:04.604
[banging on door]

10:04.647 --> 10:07.911
- Pastor Jacob? FBI.

10:10.784 --> 10:12.350
How'd the hell you get in?

10:12.394 --> 10:14.135
- Back window was open.

10:16.485 --> 10:17.834
- Two missing kids?

10:17.878 --> 10:20.315
I'd call that
exigent circumstances.

10:20.358 --> 10:22.796
- I checked the house.
Nobody's here.

10:22.839 --> 10:28.758
♪

10:28.802 --> 10:30.586
Breakfast dishes in the sink.

10:30.630 --> 10:32.675
Business as usual.

10:32.719 --> 10:34.068
Varitek's got a landline.

10:34.111 --> 10:36.287
Could be why we can't link him
to a cell number.

10:36.331 --> 10:37.941
- He's got more books
on the Antichrist

10:37.985 --> 10:40.552
than he does on Jesus.

10:40.596 --> 10:43.730
Looks like Pastor Jacob
has a little brother.

10:43.773 --> 10:45.296
- Yeah.

10:45.340 --> 10:46.689
No mom in the picture.

10:46.733 --> 10:48.125
Let's see.

10:50.388 --> 10:52.608
Yeah, Rudolph Varitek.

10:52.652 --> 10:53.957
He lives in Newbury, Vermont,

10:54.001 --> 10:55.872
a few miles
from the high school.

10:55.915 --> 10:57.961
Looks like he's got
a criminal record...

10:58.005 --> 11:00.529
in New Hampshire
for practicing medicine

11:00.572 --> 11:02.444
without a license.

11:02.487 --> 11:04.751
- Body and soul--
whatever your affliction,

11:04.794 --> 11:06.840
the Varitek brothers
got it covered.

11:08.842 --> 11:11.583
- Time to go.
We've reached our destination.

11:11.627 --> 11:13.020
- Where are you taking us?

11:13.063 --> 11:15.718
- Be patient. Let's go.

11:15.762 --> 11:18.025
Let's go.
- [roars]

11:18.068 --> 11:20.114
- Chloe!
- [screams]

11:20.157 --> 11:21.463
- Run!

11:23.770 --> 11:25.554
- Go get her!

11:25.597 --> 11:32.692
♪

11:45.748 --> 11:48.142
- Let's go.
Calm down, dear.

11:48.185 --> 11:50.535
- No, no, please!
- Please, just calm down.

11:50.579 --> 11:52.276
Just calm down.

11:52.320 --> 11:53.495
Just calm down.

11:53.538 --> 11:54.626
- Please...
- Easy.

11:54.670 --> 11:57.194
- Please. [sobbing]

11:57.238 --> 11:58.369
- All right,
think of something nice

11:58.413 --> 11:59.719
while the medicine
takes effect, huh?

11:59.762 --> 12:01.416
99,

12:01.459 --> 12:04.288
98, 97,

12:04.332 --> 12:07.683
96, 95...

12:07.727 --> 12:10.512
♪

12:15.082 --> 12:17.258
[siren wailing]

12:21.653 --> 12:23.612
- What the hell am I
supposed to tell her mother?

12:25.179 --> 12:26.789
We know how Chloe died?

12:26.833 --> 12:28.791
- EMT said there was
no sign of any violence

12:28.835 --> 12:30.184
or sexual assault.

12:30.227 --> 12:31.794
- Eh, they found ligature marks
around the wrist.

12:31.838 --> 12:33.578
- They also said
there's a pinhole tear

12:33.622 --> 12:34.754
in the shoulder of her jacket

12:34.797 --> 12:36.407
and a drop of liquid residue.

12:36.451 --> 12:38.192
- There's some dry blood
around the injection site.

12:38.235 --> 12:39.584
Could've been a hot shot.

12:39.628 --> 12:41.325
- Oh, with fake doctor
brothers involved,

12:41.369 --> 12:42.500
that would make
sense.

12:42.544 --> 12:44.633
- State M.E. will sort it out
for us.

12:44.676 --> 12:47.592
- Why grab these two kids
just to kill one of them?

12:47.636 --> 12:50.465
There's gotta be something else
going on here.

12:50.508 --> 12:51.640
- You're right.

12:51.683 --> 12:53.773
Deep dive, Rudolph Varitek.

12:53.816 --> 12:56.123
I'm gonna run a game
on Pastor Jacob

12:56.165 --> 12:57.907
and make sure we're going
down the right track.

12:57.951 --> 13:00.518
- What's the play?
- Win his trust, size him up.

13:00.562 --> 13:01.868
If he's good for this,
something will slip.

13:01.911 --> 13:03.652
- You don't need
to go undercover for that.

13:03.695 --> 13:04.871
We can just reach out
to the congregation.

13:04.914 --> 13:06.307
- We don't have time
for all that.

13:06.350 --> 13:08.265
It's a close-knit community
up here.

13:08.309 --> 13:10.267
Not a lot of love
for federal agents.

13:10.311 --> 13:11.878
I'll need a crappy car,
a Bible,

13:11.921 --> 13:13.444
and a change of clothes.

13:13.488 --> 13:17.144
[tense music]

13:17.187 --> 13:18.885
- Ah.
- Okay.

13:18.928 --> 13:21.061
- Ah.
- This'll be fine for now.

13:21.104 --> 13:22.540
I may have to suture it later.

13:22.584 --> 13:26.022
- Are you sure
no one saw you dump her?

13:26.066 --> 13:28.808
- Give me some credit.

13:28.851 --> 13:30.940
- You killed her
with that injection.

13:30.984 --> 13:32.594
- All I can get my hands on
right now

13:32.637 --> 13:34.161
are horse tranquilizers.

13:34.204 --> 13:35.727
If I had my DEA license,

13:35.771 --> 13:36.946
I would have access
to proper medication--

13:36.990 --> 13:38.469
[banging]
- Hey!

13:38.513 --> 13:40.167
Where's Chloe?
- Quiet!

13:40.210 --> 13:42.560
Quiet in there!

13:42.604 --> 13:43.997
- Where'd she go?

13:44.040 --> 13:45.389
- Quiet!

13:45.433 --> 13:52.527
♪

13:53.571 --> 13:56.313
No more miscalculations,
Rudolph.

13:56.357 --> 13:57.880
We have a lot to accomplish.

13:57.924 --> 14:00.970
Good Friday
is just around the corner.

14:01.014 --> 14:03.712
- I'll have the crosses painted
and delivered to the sanctuary.

14:03.755 --> 14:06.410
- Fine.

14:06.454 --> 14:09.370
We'll have to acquire
another she-devil.

14:09.413 --> 14:10.806
- Maybe I could just focus
on the boy.

14:10.850 --> 14:12.721
Do we really need
another female?

14:14.549 --> 14:16.899
- Eve did
the serpent's bidding

14:16.943 --> 14:20.337
and tempted Adam in the garden,

14:20.381 --> 14:23.166
so evil must be vanquished

14:23.210 --> 14:26.169
in all its incarnations.

14:26.213 --> 14:28.693
- Yes.

14:28.737 --> 14:30.652
- Maybe I can find
another girl

14:30.695 --> 14:32.480
after the funeral.

14:32.523 --> 14:34.308
We'll take him to the OR.

14:34.351 --> 14:35.483
Wait for me there.

14:35.526 --> 14:40.053
♪

14:40.096 --> 14:41.924
- Rudolph Varitek.

14:41.968 --> 14:44.535
One of the most macabre cases
I've ever prosecuted.

14:44.579 --> 14:45.710
- Because he was holding
himself out

14:45.754 --> 14:47.234
as a medical doctor?

14:47.277 --> 14:49.540
- A doctor who'd perform
the kind of elective procedures

14:49.584 --> 14:51.760
you can't get
at your corner urgent care.

14:51.803 --> 14:54.284
You ever heard
of extreme body modification?

14:54.328 --> 14:55.982
- I'm vaguely familiar, yeah.

14:56.025 --> 14:58.767
- It's more
than just stretched earlobes.

14:58.810 --> 15:02.336
Eye tattoos, tunneled cheeks
subdermal implants:

15:02.379 --> 15:03.598
Varitek did it all.

15:03.641 --> 15:05.121
- But if you wanna
disfigure yourself,

15:05.165 --> 15:06.427
isn't that legal?

15:06.470 --> 15:08.864
- He didn't stop
at cosmetics.

15:08.908 --> 15:10.997
Varitek sees himself
as an actual physician.

15:11.040 --> 15:12.955
After he flunked out
of medical school,

15:12.999 --> 15:14.870
he took up
do-it-yourself surgery

15:14.914 --> 15:16.567
on his shingle on the dark web.

15:16.611 --> 15:17.829
- He must be resentful

15:17.873 --> 15:19.396
the medical establishment
wouldn't have him.

15:19.440 --> 15:20.789
- Definitely.

15:20.832 --> 15:22.138
He wasn't even on our radar

15:22.182 --> 15:23.923
until he performed
an amateur version

15:23.966 --> 15:26.664
of gender reassignment surgery.

15:26.708 --> 15:29.754
The victim ended up in the ER
and almost died.

15:29.798 --> 15:31.756
Varitek did six months
for practicing medicine

15:31.800 --> 15:33.540
without a medical license

15:33.584 --> 15:35.630
and moved out of New Hampshire.

15:39.634 --> 15:44.247
- How do we,
as a community of believers,

15:44.290 --> 15:46.641
make peace

15:46.684 --> 15:50.079
with a senseless tragedy

15:50.123 --> 15:52.386
like the brutal death

15:52.429 --> 15:56.520
of this sweet, innocent child?

15:59.741 --> 16:03.745
I, too, have recently lost
a loved one

16:03.788 --> 16:06.269
to sinister machinations.

16:06.313 --> 16:07.967
Be assured, my good friends,

16:08.010 --> 16:10.839
these are
no random misfortunes,

16:10.882 --> 16:12.884
for the Lamb would never allow

16:12.928 --> 16:16.714
such heinous brutality
to befall the righteous,

16:16.758 --> 16:19.500
like the family that sits here
in mourning today.

16:19.543 --> 16:22.633
No, this can only be understood

16:22.677 --> 16:26.246
as the demonic work
of the Antichrist,

16:26.289 --> 16:28.378
who took this poor soul

16:28.422 --> 16:34.645
as a demonstration
of his dark, malevolent power!

16:34.689 --> 16:36.517
God bless you.

16:41.261 --> 16:44.307
- Very moving eulogy, Pastor.

16:44.351 --> 16:46.005
- Thank you.

16:46.048 --> 16:49.834
Have you also come
at the family's calling?

16:49.878 --> 16:52.446
- When I heard what happened,
I...

16:52.489 --> 16:55.101
thought I'd come
and pay my respects.

16:55.144 --> 16:56.841
- Where do you minister?

16:56.885 --> 17:01.585
- My last posting
was in Ohio, but...

17:01.629 --> 17:04.153
things didn't go so well
for me there.

17:04.196 --> 17:06.155
- How so?

17:06.199 --> 17:08.896
- I'd rather not talk about it,
if it's all the same to you.

17:08.940 --> 17:10.507
- I see.

17:10.550 --> 17:12.944
These are trying times
we live in,

17:12.988 --> 17:17.949
when men of God are themselves
treated with suspicion.

17:17.992 --> 17:20.256
- God bless you
for understanding.

17:20.300 --> 17:23.085
- Of course.

17:23.128 --> 17:27.002
- People can be
so vindictive.

17:27.046 --> 17:29.744
Your church in Dorchester--
I was hoping

17:29.787 --> 17:33.530
there might be an opportunity
there for me.

17:33.574 --> 17:36.098
- Unfortunately, there's not.

17:36.142 --> 17:39.884
We're a small
and aging congregation.

17:39.928 --> 17:41.277
As I'm sure you're aware,

17:41.321 --> 17:43.845
our youth have drifted away
from the church.

17:43.888 --> 17:46.195
- Jesus said,
"Suffer the little children,

17:46.239 --> 17:50.243
and forbid them not
to come unto me."

17:50.286 --> 17:51.896
- Easier said than done.

17:51.940 --> 17:54.377
They worship technology now.

17:54.421 --> 17:56.423
- Very true.

17:56.466 --> 17:58.381
How do we bring them back?

17:58.425 --> 18:01.297
- Show them that the work
of the devil is everywhere.

18:03.691 --> 18:05.736
Satan's cleverest trick
is to convince us

18:05.780 --> 18:09.088
he doesn't exist.

18:09.131 --> 18:12.352
We need to make evil tangible

18:12.395 --> 18:16.051
to all the doubters among us,

18:16.095 --> 18:18.575
simplify it in a way
their narrow minds

18:18.619 --> 18:20.316
can understand.

18:23.711 --> 18:26.148
- So true.

18:26.192 --> 18:29.108
Evil is everywhere.

18:29.151 --> 18:31.414
Like those
two high school students

18:31.458 --> 18:32.937
who were kidnapped

18:32.981 --> 18:35.766
across the state line.

18:35.810 --> 18:39.335
- I'm not aware
of such an incident,

18:39.379 --> 18:42.991
but I'm not one
to follow current events.

18:43.034 --> 18:45.776
You must excuse me now.

18:45.820 --> 18:47.648
I pray that you find peace

18:47.691 --> 18:51.608
and a beneficent situation.

18:51.652 --> 18:54.611
[eerie music]

18:54.655 --> 18:57.614
♪

18:57.658 --> 18:58.920
- I just spent
some quality time

18:58.963 --> 19:00.748
with Pastor Jacob.

19:00.791 --> 19:02.619
He's obsessed with this dude
named Satan.

19:02.663 --> 19:05.753
My gut tells me he's in this
up to his clerical collar.

19:05.796 --> 19:07.885
- Security footage puts
Rudolph's Chevy

19:07.929 --> 19:09.278
at the high school parking lot

19:09.322 --> 19:10.975
ten minutes
before the abduction.

19:11.019 --> 19:12.194
- Where's Rudolph now?

19:12.238 --> 19:13.848
- We still don't have
a 20 on him.

19:13.891 --> 19:15.893
- Get a drone with
thermal imaging capability

19:15.937 --> 19:17.939
over the Variteks' property.
That church too.

19:17.982 --> 19:19.114
- Okay, copy that.

19:19.158 --> 19:20.376
- And someone
was recently killed

19:20.420 --> 19:22.509
in Jacob's family--
a crime victim, maybe.

19:22.552 --> 19:23.901
Suss that out.
In the meantime,

19:23.945 --> 19:25.076
I'm gonna stay on Jacob.

19:25.120 --> 19:26.991
- Okay.

19:27.035 --> 19:29.168
You want some company?

19:29.211 --> 19:30.778
- You think I need
a babysitter?

19:30.821 --> 19:32.040
- Well, I saw your eyes

19:32.083 --> 19:33.998
when you lied
to those families.

19:34.042 --> 19:37.132
I know this one's hitting
close to home.

19:37.176 --> 19:39.178
- I'm good.

19:39.221 --> 19:42.050
Jacob's gonna screw up
and lead us straight to Luke.

19:42.093 --> 19:44.226
I gotta go.
- [sighs]

19:44.270 --> 19:47.229
[tense music]

19:47.273 --> 19:52.930
♪

19:52.974 --> 19:56.978
- [breathing shakily]

19:58.675 --> 19:59.894
- Hey.

20:01.765 --> 20:04.507
- What did you do with Chloe?

20:04.551 --> 20:06.205
- Don't worry, son.

20:06.248 --> 20:07.206
She's fine.

20:08.946 --> 20:11.993
- I don't believe you.

20:12.036 --> 20:13.690
- Why would I wanna hurt her?

20:13.734 --> 20:15.736
I made you a sandwich.

20:15.779 --> 20:17.346
Enjoy it.

20:17.390 --> 20:21.307
It's the last solid food
you'll have for some time.

20:21.350 --> 20:22.525
- [whimpers]

20:22.569 --> 20:29.489
♪

20:44.678 --> 20:46.984
- Be a good boy
for Dr. Rudolph.

20:47.028 --> 20:48.551
Stick out your tongue.

20:48.595 --> 20:49.987
- No, please.

20:50.031 --> 20:52.163
- This is going to happen
one way or another.

20:52.207 --> 20:54.122
If you don't cooperate,
it's just going to make things

20:54.165 --> 20:56.429
a lot more unpleasant

20:56.472 --> 20:57.821
for both of us.

21:00.737 --> 21:02.435
Come closer.

21:08.354 --> 21:09.485
Good boy.

21:12.923 --> 21:15.186
Lovely.

21:15.230 --> 21:16.971
I think
this'll work out nicely.

21:20.017 --> 21:21.976
We'll begin when Jacob returns.

21:26.328 --> 21:29.288
- [sobbing]

21:29.331 --> 21:32.291
♪

21:36.164 --> 21:37.992
- Jacob's still on the road.

21:38.035 --> 21:39.341
Driving south.

21:39.385 --> 21:41.387
- Air ops did infrared scans
of the Variteks'.

21:41.430 --> 21:42.736
Results are negative.

21:42.779 --> 21:44.390
- What about the church?
- Same deal.

21:44.433 --> 21:45.608
But I did find an obituary

21:45.652 --> 21:47.131
on the Variteks' father,
Douglas.

21:47.175 --> 21:48.698
Now, he died five months ago

21:48.742 --> 21:51.048
after a lengthy battle
with Behcet's disease.

21:51.092 --> 21:52.746
- Never heard of it.

21:52.789 --> 21:54.051
- We'll I'll spare you
all the gory details,

21:54.095 --> 21:55.662
but it's a long and painful way
to go,

21:55.705 --> 21:57.664
something that I'm sure
would've been difficult

21:57.707 --> 21:58.839
to watch their father
go through.

21:58.882 --> 22:01.581
- Interesting.

22:01.624 --> 22:03.757
Hana, hang on a second.
Claire, what's up?

22:03.800 --> 22:05.585
- I'm sorry to bother you
while you're working,

22:05.628 --> 22:07.804
but I thought
you would wanna hear this.

22:07.848 --> 22:10.590
The Florida commission
turned down Davis' request

22:10.633 --> 22:14.202
for compassionate
medical release.

22:14.245 --> 22:15.769
- That's great news.

22:15.812 --> 22:17.771
- I don't know what you said
to them down there, Remy,

22:17.814 --> 22:20.861
but I guess they made
the right decision.

22:20.904 --> 22:22.384
[car horn blares]

22:22.428 --> 22:24.647
- Sorry. Do you need a lift?

22:26.562 --> 22:27.998
- Claire, I gotta go.
I'll hit you later.

22:28.042 --> 22:29.957
Hana, tell Kristin to write
a haul-ass order

22:30.000 --> 22:32.046
to my location.
- What's going on?

22:32.089 --> 22:34.309
- Looks like Jacob
just kidnapped another girl.

22:34.353 --> 22:37.443
[tense music]

22:37.486 --> 22:39.183
[honks horn]

22:39.227 --> 22:42.448
♪

22:42.491 --> 22:43.927
Pastor Jacob.

22:43.971 --> 22:46.365
I was just driving by,
and I noticed your van.

22:47.975 --> 22:49.063
- Hello again.

22:49.106 --> 22:50.064
- Is that your daughter?

22:50.107 --> 22:51.152
- [laughs]

22:51.195 --> 22:52.414
- Oh. Oh, no.

22:52.458 --> 22:54.285
This is Amanda.

22:54.329 --> 22:57.201
She's the granddaughter
of one of our congregants.

22:57.245 --> 22:58.725
- Nice to meet you, Father.

22:58.768 --> 23:00.379
- Nice to meet you as well.

23:00.422 --> 23:01.815
How's your day going, Amanda?

23:01.858 --> 23:03.033
- Great.

23:03.077 --> 23:05.035
Pastor Jacob just saw me
leaving the diner,

23:05.079 --> 23:07.342
and he was nice enough
to offer me a ride home.

23:07.386 --> 23:08.691
- So nice.
- Hmm.

23:11.259 --> 23:12.434
You know what, Amanda?

23:12.478 --> 23:14.697
My stomach is starting
to growl.

23:14.741 --> 23:18.092
I'm craving one of Gus'
meatloaf sandwiches.

23:18.135 --> 23:20.311
I'm sorry, I'm gonna have to
send you on your way.

23:20.355 --> 23:21.312
- Oh, okay.

23:21.356 --> 23:22.966
Yeah. [laughs]

23:23.010 --> 23:25.360
- Sorry about that.
- It's okay.

23:25.404 --> 23:27.101
- Bye, Amanda!
- Bye!

23:27.144 --> 23:28.668
Nice to see you, Pastor Jacob.

23:28.711 --> 23:30.583
- Nice to see you too.

23:30.626 --> 23:32.280
Get home safe, huh?

23:32.323 --> 23:33.455
- Thank you. I will.

23:33.499 --> 23:34.630
- Okay.

23:34.674 --> 23:36.589
Bye-bye.
- Bye.

23:36.632 --> 23:38.068
- Such a beautiful day, huh?

23:39.896 --> 23:42.072
- You know,
I didn't catch your name.

23:42.116 --> 23:43.813
- Remy,

23:43.857 --> 23:45.336
like the cognac.

23:45.380 --> 23:47.730
Dark and smooth.

23:47.774 --> 23:50.516
[laughs]

23:50.559 --> 23:52.126
- Well, good day
to you, Remy.

23:52.169 --> 23:55.651
- And the Lord be with you.

23:55.695 --> 23:57.392
- Safe travels.

23:57.436 --> 24:04.573
♪

24:12.363 --> 24:13.756
- Thank you.
- Sure.

24:16.629 --> 24:18.761
- Mind if I join?

24:18.805 --> 24:21.503
- I was hoping to have
a few moments to myself.

24:23.679 --> 24:26.247
- You said the meatloaf's
good here.

24:26.290 --> 24:27.727
I'm a sucker for chopped meat.

24:27.770 --> 24:29.206
- I'm sure you'll enjoy it,

24:29.250 --> 24:30.904
but at another table, please.

24:30.947 --> 24:32.906
- You know,
I can't help thinking

24:32.949 --> 24:35.865
maybe Amanda shouldn't
be walking home alone today.

24:35.909 --> 24:38.128
- I'm sure she'll be fine.
- I'm not.

24:38.172 --> 24:40.479
I heard on the radio
that the girl who was kidnapped

24:40.522 --> 24:42.785
in Vermont was found dead

24:42.829 --> 24:44.395
not too far from here.

24:44.439 --> 24:45.440
- That's a shame.

24:45.484 --> 24:48.356
- But the boy
she was with?

24:48.399 --> 24:49.923
Still missing.
- Mm.

24:49.966 --> 24:51.664
- Why do you think
they'd keep him alive

24:51.707 --> 24:53.230
but kill her?

24:53.274 --> 24:55.494
- There are some evils
we can't begin to understand.

24:55.537 --> 24:56.973
- [laughs]

24:57.017 --> 24:59.236
It's so funny
you should say that,

24:59.280 --> 25:02.022
because I always wrestle
with that question.

25:02.065 --> 25:05.329
Do sinners believe
they're evil,

25:05.373 --> 25:07.680
or do they have
rationalizations

25:07.723 --> 25:10.465
that excuse their damage?

25:10.509 --> 25:15.949
- Only God knows
what's inside a person.

25:15.992 --> 25:19.126
- But what do you think, Jacob?

25:19.169 --> 25:22.433
Could there be
some heartbreaking event

25:22.477 --> 25:25.698
that set these crimes
in motion?

25:25.741 --> 25:27.438
- [laughs nervously] Excuse me.

25:27.482 --> 25:34.533
♪

25:52.333 --> 25:54.509
- I believe the Lord
brought us together

25:54.553 --> 25:56.511
for a divine purpose, Jacob:

25:56.555 --> 25:58.078
to help this boy

25:58.121 --> 25:59.079
who's trapped somewhere.

25:59.122 --> 26:00.559
- I'd like some privacy,
please.

26:00.602 --> 26:01.690
- If you'd rather not talk,

26:01.734 --> 26:04.606
let's at least invoke the power

26:04.650 --> 26:06.173
of our joint prayer.

26:06.216 --> 26:08.523
Let's kneel

26:08.567 --> 26:10.090
and pray together.

26:10.133 --> 26:12.483
Please, Lord,

26:12.527 --> 26:14.834
save this boy.

26:14.877 --> 26:18.359
Save him.
Say it with me, Jacob.

26:18.402 --> 26:20.491
Save him.

26:20.535 --> 26:23.407
- Save him.

26:23.451 --> 26:27.716
- Let's also pray
for his captors,

26:27.760 --> 26:32.634
that they see the error
of their ways,

26:32.678 --> 26:37.726
that they repent
and find grace in the Lord.

26:37.770 --> 26:40.599
♪

26:40.642 --> 26:42.557
[crying] I can't imagine

26:42.601 --> 26:46.387
what this boy is going through,

26:46.430 --> 26:49.042
his hands bound together.

26:49.085 --> 26:52.567
His family feels the same pain

26:52.611 --> 26:53.873
that you must have felt

26:53.916 --> 26:56.919
when you lost your father,
Jacob.

26:56.963 --> 26:59.705
So much sorrow, I'm sure.

26:59.748 --> 27:01.271
Oh.

27:02.838 --> 27:05.798
There's still time
for you to renounce this evil

27:05.841 --> 27:09.236
and reach out
for His forgiveness.

27:09.279 --> 27:11.325
- Get your hands off me.

27:11.368 --> 27:18.245
♪

27:18.288 --> 27:20.334
- Let's cleanse ourselves,
you and I both.

27:24.033 --> 27:25.252
- [groans]
- It's time for us

27:25.295 --> 27:26.775
to atone for our sins.
- You're hurting me.

27:26.819 --> 27:28.081
[knock on door]
- Get off!

27:28.124 --> 27:29.604
- Is everything all right
in there?

27:29.648 --> 27:36.002
♪

27:36.045 --> 27:39.092
- We can't run
from the evil we do, Jacob.

27:39.135 --> 27:42.443
The Lord is commanding you
to renounce Satan

27:42.486 --> 27:44.097
and be saved.

27:44.140 --> 27:47.230
Save yourself, Jacob.
Save your soul.

27:47.274 --> 27:50.190
Save your soul, Jacob.
Save your soul!

27:50.233 --> 27:51.844
Save your soul!

27:51.887 --> 27:55.804
♪

27:55.848 --> 27:57.545
We're just gonna let him
drive away?

27:57.588 --> 27:59.590
- We don't have enough
to hold him on right now, Remy.

27:59.634 --> 28:01.288
There are rules--
- Throw the rules!

28:01.331 --> 28:04.073
He's got Luke,
he and his psycho brother.

28:04.117 --> 28:05.640
- What the hell were you
trying to do in there?

28:05.684 --> 28:06.772
- Conducting an inquisition,

28:06.815 --> 28:08.643
trying to get him to confess.

28:08.687 --> 28:10.558
- We did that, like,
600 years ago.

28:10.601 --> 28:13.213
- If they kill Luke now,
it's on us.

28:13.256 --> 28:14.954
- You wanna live
with his blood on your hands?

28:14.997 --> 28:16.390
- Hey, listen to me.
I know this is what happened

28:16.433 --> 28:17.608
to your brother.

28:17.652 --> 28:19.262
Okay?

28:19.306 --> 28:21.830
- Just give me ten more minutes
alone with him,

28:21.874 --> 28:23.658
and this can all be over.

28:23.702 --> 28:25.051
- This feels personal.
I've been there.

28:25.094 --> 28:26.748
I get it, okay?
But we gotta take a step back,

28:26.792 --> 28:27.793
take a deep breath.

28:27.836 --> 28:29.011
We'll send Ray to follow him.

28:29.055 --> 28:29.969
He's not gonna do anything
to Luke

28:30.012 --> 28:31.405
with a tail on him.

28:31.448 --> 28:33.233
All right?

28:33.276 --> 28:35.365
- Take my car.

28:38.455 --> 28:40.980
I just wanna nail this son
of a bitch to the cross.

28:41.023 --> 28:42.895
- I hear you,
and we will, okay?

28:42.938 --> 28:47.073
♪

28:47.116 --> 28:48.857
We will.

28:55.472 --> 28:57.431
[tense music]

28:57.474 --> 28:59.172
- Where is Jacob now?

28:59.215 --> 29:01.304
- He's on his way back
to the church.

29:01.348 --> 29:03.176
Doesn't seem like
he's in a hurry, though.

29:03.219 --> 29:05.221
- All right, keep us posted.

29:05.265 --> 29:06.309
Mr. Spottiswood.

29:06.353 --> 29:07.658
- You said you'd be in touch.

29:07.702 --> 29:10.313
- Yeah, um,
come over here for a second.

29:12.533 --> 29:14.187
Things are moving very quickly.

29:14.230 --> 29:15.492
- So you know where Luke is.

29:15.536 --> 29:17.277
- We're doing everything
in our power

29:17.320 --> 29:18.582
to bring him home safely.

29:21.107 --> 29:23.979
- He's gonna end up in a ditch
like Chloe, isn't he?

29:24.023 --> 29:25.981
- Listen to me--
- [cries]

29:26.025 --> 29:27.113
- I know these have been

29:27.156 --> 29:29.202
the worst two days
of your life,

29:29.245 --> 29:30.594
but there's nothing
you can do about it

29:30.638 --> 29:33.684
but go home, take care
of yourself and your wife.

29:33.728 --> 29:35.295
I have a team with some
of the best agents

29:35.338 --> 29:37.688
in the bureau with me, and we
have some very strong leads.

29:37.732 --> 29:39.734
- What kind of person
would do this to them?

29:41.692 --> 29:43.042
- Go home.

29:43.085 --> 29:46.175
As soon as something breaks,
I'll let you know.

29:46.219 --> 29:47.698
Will you do that for me?

29:47.742 --> 29:51.702
♪

29:51.746 --> 29:53.966
- I'm sorry for barging in here
like a crazy person.

29:54.009 --> 29:56.446
I just--I feel so helpless.

29:56.490 --> 29:58.144
- No need to apologize.

29:58.187 --> 30:00.755
It's your son. I get it.

30:00.799 --> 30:02.365
Go home.

30:02.409 --> 30:08.589
♪

30:08.632 --> 30:11.331
Okay, so we have Jacob pinned.

30:11.374 --> 30:12.723
Why can't we find his brother?

30:12.767 --> 30:14.725
- No friends, no family,
no social media.

30:14.769 --> 30:16.510
- We have to think
outside the box.

30:16.553 --> 30:17.990
We're running out of time.

30:18.033 --> 30:19.513
- What about
the caretaker at the church?

30:19.556 --> 30:20.557
- Well, Ray and I
didn't get much.

30:20.601 --> 30:21.863
He's a man of few words.

30:21.907 --> 30:23.996
- I'll have Hana take
another crack at him.

30:26.433 --> 30:28.043
- I already told
your two Black friends

30:28.087 --> 30:29.740
where to find the pastor.

30:29.784 --> 30:31.090
- Right.

30:31.133 --> 30:33.832
Have you seen his brother,
Rudolph?

30:33.875 --> 30:36.573
- Lives in Vermont.
- I'm aware.

30:36.617 --> 30:39.881
But when was the last time
Rudolph was here?

30:39.925 --> 30:41.622
- Hard to say.

30:45.104 --> 30:48.237
- What's M-I-C?

30:48.281 --> 30:50.544
- McKerry Industrial Chemicals.

30:50.587 --> 30:53.068
Worked there for 39 years.

30:53.112 --> 30:55.201
- Hazardous chemicals.

30:55.244 --> 30:56.463
Must've been a tough job.

30:56.506 --> 30:57.681
- Damn right, it was.

30:57.725 --> 30:59.901
That's how I know the Variteks.

30:59.945 --> 31:01.468
Jacob gave me
some work around the church

31:01.511 --> 31:02.904
after I retired.

31:02.948 --> 31:04.514
- He worked with you?

31:04.558 --> 31:08.518
- His father did, Douglas,

31:08.562 --> 31:11.521
till he got sick
and went on disability

31:11.565 --> 31:13.784
a few years
before the plant closed.

31:13.828 --> 31:16.178
- Ah, he had, uh,
Behcet's disease.

31:16.222 --> 31:17.919
- All I know is,
the doctors up here

31:17.963 --> 31:19.181
couldn't do much for him.

31:19.225 --> 31:21.618
Took its toll on the brothers,

31:21.662 --> 31:24.795
seeing their father suffer
and waste away like that.

31:24.839 --> 31:28.669
It drove Jacob to a dark place
with his ministry.

31:28.712 --> 31:31.063
He could only understand
his father's torture

31:31.106 --> 31:33.065
as something that was evil.

31:33.108 --> 31:35.850
- So there's
an abandoned chemical plant

31:35.894 --> 31:38.635
'round here?

31:38.679 --> 31:40.028
- They turned the place
inside out.

31:40.072 --> 31:41.943
Nothing but rusty pipes
and empty storage tanks.

31:41.987 --> 31:43.684
- They have to be hiding
somewhere in there.

31:43.727 --> 31:45.294
- Pull everybody out
and search it all over again.

31:45.338 --> 31:46.643
- It's a lot of manpower
to tie up.

31:46.687 --> 31:48.210
- They have something better
to do?

31:48.254 --> 31:50.473
Or maybe tunnels
we don't know about,

31:50.517 --> 31:52.214
underground tanks?
Who the hell knows?

31:52.258 --> 31:54.303
- Okay, I'll let them know.

31:54.347 --> 31:55.652
- What is that thing?

31:55.696 --> 31:58.612
- I don't know.
- Let's check it.

31:58.655 --> 32:04.923
♪

32:06.228 --> 32:09.188
- The lock and chain
looks new.

32:09.231 --> 32:11.451
- Stand back.

32:31.384 --> 32:33.690
- Boot must've been here.

32:33.734 --> 32:35.388
- Somebody
must've tipped him off.

32:37.216 --> 32:38.304
What's back here?

32:38.347 --> 32:45.441
♪

32:53.058 --> 32:54.842
- Oh, God.

32:59.238 --> 33:01.196
- Horns?

33:01.240 --> 33:03.590
Clawed hands.

33:04.678 --> 33:07.376
These twisted bastards.

33:07.420 --> 33:09.248
They're turning Luke
into the devil.

33:09.291 --> 33:15.167
♪

33:21.042 --> 33:23.088
- This is terrifying.

33:23.131 --> 33:25.394
To inflict this level
of deformity

33:25.438 --> 33:28.180
on another human being--
it's a long way from religion.

33:28.223 --> 33:30.225
- Their father's death
must've really screwed them up.

33:30.269 --> 33:31.705
Maybe the only thing
they could blame for his death

33:31.748 --> 33:32.793
was the Antichrist.

33:32.836 --> 33:34.055
- So what's their endgame?

33:34.099 --> 33:36.188
Just turn Luke into a freak?

33:36.231 --> 33:37.972
[cell phone rings]
Parade him around on Sundays

33:38.016 --> 33:40.453
like some sort
of proof of concept?

33:40.496 --> 33:41.715
- Ray.

33:41.758 --> 33:42.803
- Jacob's leaving the church.

33:42.846 --> 33:44.065
He just got in his van.

33:44.109 --> 33:46.285
Looks like he's heading north
on Route 117.

33:46.328 --> 33:48.722
- Okay, he might be on his way
to Rudolph and Luke.

33:48.765 --> 33:49.853
We found their hideout.

33:49.897 --> 33:51.072
Looks like they left
in a hurry.

33:51.116 --> 33:52.552
- Hana, is there any chance

33:52.595 --> 33:54.075
that Rudolph and Luke
could've slipped in the church

33:54.119 --> 33:56.034
while Jacob led us
all over New Hampshire?

33:56.077 --> 33:58.558
- Uh, there's a road that goes
around the back of the ridge.

33:58.601 --> 34:00.386
It'd be about a ten-minute hike
through the woods.

34:00.429 --> 34:01.822
- Ray, get in that church.

34:01.865 --> 34:03.519
- What about Jacob?
- We'll intercept him.

34:03.563 --> 34:05.869
Just get in that church
and tear it apart.

34:05.913 --> 34:07.436
- But the church
is probably locked.

34:07.480 --> 34:08.916
- Then kick
the damn door down!

34:08.958 --> 34:11.223
[tense music]

34:11.266 --> 34:12.789
[engine turns over]

34:12.833 --> 34:16.576
♪

34:16.619 --> 34:18.317
- [panting]

34:18.360 --> 34:21.494
- Jacob was going to be here
with a female companion for you

34:21.536 --> 34:23.452
and to bless
your transformation

34:23.496 --> 34:26.498
with a prayer, but that doesn't
seem to be happening,

34:26.542 --> 34:28.109
so we're going to begin
without him.

34:28.152 --> 34:31.112
- No!
- Try to relax, Luke.

34:31.156 --> 34:33.114
All right?
I promise to be gentle,

34:33.158 --> 34:34.811
and it's better
if you don't resist.

34:34.855 --> 34:37.597
- [crying out indistinctly]

34:37.639 --> 34:39.251
- This'll all be over
very soon,

34:39.293 --> 34:40.991
and you can focus on healing.

34:41.034 --> 34:42.210
- No.
- Let's begin.

34:42.254 --> 34:44.429
- [crying] No! No!

34:44.473 --> 34:51.393
♪

34:56.094 --> 34:57.660
[distant clatter]

34:57.704 --> 34:59.097
- If you make a sound,

34:59.140 --> 35:01.142
I will slice your throat
from ear to ear.

35:01.186 --> 35:08.323
♪

35:15.983 --> 35:17.332
- Damn.

35:22.337 --> 35:24.034
- Are you seeing this?
- Yes.

35:24.078 --> 35:26.820
- They've erected two crosses
in the back of the church.

35:26.863 --> 35:28.300
Black ones.

35:28.343 --> 35:29.475
- Yeah, with nails
at the ready.

35:29.518 --> 35:31.303
- Pfft.
- So that was their plan:

35:31.346 --> 35:33.043
to crucify the Antichrist
they conjured

35:33.087 --> 35:34.741
by mutilating those kids.

35:39.224 --> 35:41.661
[distant clatter]

35:41.704 --> 35:48.668
♪

35:59.200 --> 36:02.334
[siren wailing]

36:06.251 --> 36:08.122
- I'll get local PD
to put down a spike strip

36:08.166 --> 36:09.428
and road block up ahead.

36:09.471 --> 36:11.125
- Kristin?
- Yeah.

36:11.169 --> 36:12.300
- I want this bitch alive

36:12.344 --> 36:13.997
so I can look him
in the eye again.

36:14.041 --> 36:21.179
♪

36:38.587 --> 36:39.588
- [yells]

37:03.133 --> 37:04.744
- You're safe, all right?

37:04.787 --> 37:06.093
I'm with the FBI.

37:06.136 --> 37:07.921
- [crying]

37:07.964 --> 37:09.705
- You're safe.
I got you.

37:09.749 --> 37:12.012
All right?
Come on, come on, come on.

37:12.055 --> 37:13.622
All right? All right?

37:15.972 --> 37:17.235
You good?

37:18.627 --> 37:21.239
I got you. I got you, man.
I got you, okay?

37:22.979 --> 37:29.551
♪

38:20.036 --> 38:23.301
- [groaning]

38:31.700 --> 38:33.746
- Don't move!

38:33.789 --> 38:34.964
On the ground.

38:36.966 --> 38:39.012
Show me your hands.

38:39.055 --> 38:40.100
- You.

38:40.143 --> 38:42.363
You deceived me.

38:47.107 --> 38:49.283
- Don't move.
- Impostor.

38:49.327 --> 38:56.421
♪

38:58.901 --> 39:00.512
Agent of Satan!

39:00.555 --> 39:01.861
Gah!

39:10.348 --> 39:11.610
- He's dead.

39:13.786 --> 39:14.917
Good riddance.

39:14.961 --> 39:16.223
- Ray confirmed.

39:16.266 --> 39:18.138
Rudolph's dead too.

39:18.181 --> 39:19.313
- Luke?

39:19.357 --> 39:21.228
- He's okay.
Not a mark on him.

39:21.271 --> 39:24.362
- [sighs] I'll call his father.

39:24.405 --> 39:27.060
We saved one kid today.

39:27.103 --> 39:29.062
Wish it could've been two.

39:29.105 --> 39:36.025
♪

39:39.551 --> 39:43.424
[cell phone ringing]

39:43.468 --> 39:45.208
Hey, Georgie.

39:45.252 --> 39:47.907
Who?

39:47.950 --> 39:49.822
Yeah, send her up.

39:51.867 --> 39:53.260
- Agent Scott.

39:53.303 --> 39:54.435
I'm Serena Wade.

39:54.479 --> 39:56.219
I saw you
at the Larry Davis hearing

39:56.263 --> 39:57.569
in Florida.
- I remember.

39:57.612 --> 39:58.700
Are you his family?

39:58.744 --> 40:00.746
- No,
I'm a documentary filmmaker.

40:00.789 --> 40:02.574
I actually live here
in New York.

40:02.617 --> 40:04.053
Do you mind if we talk
for a minute?

40:04.097 --> 40:07.187
Won't take long.

40:07.230 --> 40:09.755
I wanted to give you
a heads-up.

40:09.798 --> 40:13.367
Did you hear
about the rule 3.850 filing?

40:13.411 --> 40:15.282
- The what?
- It's a motion

40:15.325 --> 40:16.631
for post-conviction relief.

40:16.675 --> 40:19.199
It was filed in Broward County
yesterday

40:19.242 --> 40:20.635
on Larry Davis' behalf.

40:23.333 --> 40:25.118
- They're asking
for a new trial?

40:25.161 --> 40:27.773
- Yes.

40:27.816 --> 40:28.991
- Based on what?

40:29.035 --> 40:30.602
- Actual innocence.

40:30.645 --> 40:33.866
He claimed the prosecutor
withheld exculpatory evidence

40:33.909 --> 40:35.694
among other things.

40:37.957 --> 40:40.612
- Are his lawyers getting paid
by the word?

40:40.655 --> 40:42.135
- They're not getting paid
at all.

40:42.178 --> 40:44.006
They're from
the Florida Innocence Project.

40:44.050 --> 40:45.486
- Well, they're wasting
their time.

40:45.530 --> 40:47.227
The case against Davis
was airtight.

40:47.270 --> 40:48.533
- You remember
the state attorney

40:48.576 --> 40:49.751
who prosecuted the case?

40:49.795 --> 40:51.623
Brody Birch?
- What about him?

40:51.666 --> 40:52.798
- I started looking into him

40:52.841 --> 40:54.713
after several complaints
were filed

40:54.756 --> 40:56.497
to the state bar last year.

40:56.541 --> 40:58.499
A white prosecutor who targeted

40:58.543 --> 41:00.806
mostly
African American defendants.

41:00.849 --> 41:03.330
At first, I thought this was
a story about race,

41:03.373 --> 41:04.810
but the deeper that I dug,

41:04.853 --> 41:07.334
the more I realized
this is pure corruption.

41:07.377 --> 41:09.641
Brady violations,
witness tampering--

41:09.684 --> 41:11.164
I mean, who knows
how many innocent people

41:11.207 --> 41:12.557
this guy has put behind bars?

41:12.600 --> 41:14.733
- What does this have to do
with me?

41:14.776 --> 41:17.866
- I wanna make Davis' appeal
the center of my film,

41:17.910 --> 41:19.520
follow it from beginning
to end,

41:19.564 --> 41:21.827
and I'd like for you
to get involved.

41:21.870 --> 41:24.046
I need someone who can humanize
the victim

41:24.090 --> 41:27.659
and speak on his behalf.

41:27.702 --> 41:30.444
- I don't give a damn
about your film

41:30.488 --> 41:32.054
or what you need.

41:32.098 --> 41:34.535
- Well, I'm not
taking sides here.

41:34.579 --> 41:36.363
I don't know
how this is gonna end

41:36.406 --> 41:37.669
or where this is gonna go.

41:37.712 --> 41:39.192
I just think that this is
a compelling story.

41:39.235 --> 41:41.716
- How nice for you.

41:41.760 --> 41:43.675
- You said at the hearing,

41:43.718 --> 41:45.677
"Let justice be served."

41:45.720 --> 41:48.157
What if he didn't do it?
- But he did do it.

41:49.594 --> 41:51.247
And he's not getting out.

41:51.291 --> 41:53.032
That's your story.

41:53.075 --> 41:55.556
And you should leave.

41:55.600 --> 41:57.036
- I didn't mean to offend you.

41:57.079 --> 41:59.691
I just...

41:59.734 --> 42:01.736
- Good night.
- Well... [sighs]

42:01.780 --> 42:04.391
In case you change your mind--
- I won't.

42:04.434 --> 42:11.137
♪

42:27.893 --> 42:30.809
[dramatic music]

42:30.852 --> 42:37.990
♪

42:47.434 --> 42:49.088
[wolf howls]
